features: 【Ergonomic Healthy Style】The ergonomic electric standing desk allows you to release your hands and effortlessly customize the desired height between 28.7''- 48''. With a high-quality motor, our adjustable desk operates quietly at less than 55dB and can be used with confidence even in the quietest room.

【Precise & Stable Adjustment】Designed to cater to your needs, our stand up desk design features an LED display and 3 memory presets, helping you make precise and quick adjustments. The robust wooden desktop and the T-shaped steel frame ensure maximum stability and can hold up to 176 lbs.

【Suitable for Daily Use】 Stay organized with our sit stand desk which comes equipped with 2 hooks on either side and 2 wire collecting holes on the desktop, making it an easy and convenient option for daily use. The eco-friendly wood is sleek, easy to clean, and odor-free.

【More Choices】Our stand up desk is available in a range of colors and sizes, making it an ideal choice for a computer desk, writing desk and more. Whether it's in your living room, study, bedroom, or any other space, it's always a great addition.

【Easy Assembly】The package includes a height adjustable desk, an instruction manual, and necessary tools for assembly. You can easily put it together using our installation video. Please note that the table top consists of two pieces, which need to be installed and connected.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to assemble
reviews.reviewText: I put this desk together by myself in 45 minutes. The instructions are clear, all the pieces lined up perfectly, and I didn’t have any issues with screwing things in. I do recommend to use a bigger screwdriver than the one it comes in with it you have one to avoid hand cramping! Overall it was an easy process and I am happy with the purchase. Easy to program the height settings and looks really good and sturdy. The price can’t be beat.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great for a variety of people
reviews.reviewText: After looking at a standing desk for a long time and having this model on my wishlist for some time, I bought it. The instructions were ok but at least one of the pictures mirrored. Once together it is fairly sturdy, and goes smoothly up and down. I also like that there are three memory settings and they work flawless.My only concern is that the table top consists of two parts, held together by the end pieces and some metal pieces at 4 points. There is a noticable line across the table where the two pieces meet and it flexes when you're leaning on the table. Time will tell if it will be an issue.Other then that the legs are heavy and solid, the motor moves the desk up and down without issue, and I am pretty happy with it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Slight shipping damage, easy assembly
reviews.reviewText: This desk was very easy to assemble. The instructions were clear and had pictures for visual learners which was really helpful.The legs/ stand portion of the desk are heavy, durable, and create. Stable desk but the two pieces that create the desk top are not the highest quality. In fact, there is a slight dent right in the center of the desktop. It wouldn’t be worth it to disassemble and return. It’s a small enough dent that isn’t paint chipped so I can live with it.It adjusts just like it is advertised. I also purchased a walking treadmill for underneath standing desks, so this is a perfect match for that product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy table, great price!!
reviews.reviewText: Didn't take long to assemble. Set up was easy. 3 modes you can set to specific heights. The motor isn't loud. Doesn't shake or wobble. The lowest height you can get is 73.0 (inches). The under desk headset holder is closer to the middle of the side edges, but very convenient for other cables/etc if you don't have to rush to pick up the phone asap. The desk itself is split in half length-wise for ease of shipping/packaging, and I have not noticed the split at all. It's super seamless, smooth.Also, the 73.0 inch base desk setting fits well for a gaming chair, specifically the Secretlab one. I don't find the trouble of the desk being too high for my gaming chair when I want to sit down. (I have the medium/regular-sized Secretlab chair, not the XL one or small one.) 77.0 inches is the perfect desk height for the Secretlab chair to slide under the lowest setting with the chair dropped all the way down and the armrests raised by 2 notches.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is an outstanding desk! Meets all my expectations! Easy to put together! Maybe took 25 minutes that is with unboxing. Super simple. Itnis perfect! It moves up and down. I can sit down and work or raise the desk up and work. It is really soft and smooth top! You can tell it is very well made! I really like it! I also love the child lock feature since I have kids.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy assembly - love it!
reviews.reviewText: I was able to put this together with no help in about an hour. Highly recommend using a drill. Love the rustic wood color. Being able to save 3 different height settings is nice. Overall I’m very pleased with this purchase. The quality is great as well!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Decent desk for what I need
reviews.reviewText: Item arrived with minor damage to one of the top boards in a few places along the middle edge. It's not bad, but disappointing. Item is very easy to install The unit goes up and down with ease. It is not the most stable desk and tends to move back and forth pretty easily. Just be cautious of what you put on it. (ie: don't put drinks on the unit). But, for what I need it for, it works fine.If you plan to put a keyboard tray on the bottom, you will need to build out the bottom so the tray has something to attach to because all the mechanical components for the riser are otherwise in the way. I did this in 3 steps because the desktop itself is only 5/8" thick so you don't have much to work with on the first piece of plywood. In my case, I stacked 2 pieces of 3/4" plywood and 1 piece of 1/4" plywood in front and behind the bars to give room for the keyboard tray. If you leave the keyboard on the desktop, you will have no issues.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good quality for the price
reviews.reviewText: I received the desk last week and took about 2 hours to put together. I made one mistake assembling it which cost me a little time. The frame is sturdy and was easy to assemble. No problems with alignment of holes which some have complained about. Only time will tell if the electrical will hold out and I will update my review after a few months. There was one hole in the package where the was nothing solid inside so there was no damage to the product. The top is a bit flimsy, laminate over particle board, but quality I expected for the price.I wish there was a way to switch the side the controls are on, it would work better for my set up and I will have to decide if I want to drill new holes for that.

I shopped for a very long time before picking this one converter. I work from home most days and didn't want to replace my whole desk. This converter holds my main screen as well as my laptop and laptop stand to use as a second screen. The whole thing is very comfortable, extremely easy to bring up and down, and very sturdy. I've had it for seven months now and it still looks new after near-daily usage. My only complaint is that it only comes in black!
